          API Documentation for Multi Monitors Activex Control

CLSID is : "2182DB6C-70D2-48E8-AE6C-6DE4816B1DF2".


Introduction

    This documents the programming interface to Multi Monitors Ctrl ActiveX control.


It exposes 8 Methods:

1. Method:
    FullScreen(); (It is used to display IE in fullscreen mode.)
   
           Parameters:
    	     None.
    
           Returns:
 	     None.

2. Method:
    GetMonitorCount([out, retval] long *a_plMonitorCount); (It is used to get the Monitor                                          count.).
   
           Parameters:
    	     None.
    
           Returns:
 	     Positive Integer.

3. Method:
    GetMonitorLeft([in] long a_lMonID, [out, retval] long *a_plMonitorLeft); (It is used to get                               the left co-ordinate of a particular monitor.)
   
           Parameters:
    	     Positive Integer.(Monitor index. It should start from "0")
    
           Returns:
 	     Positive Integer.

4. Method:
    GetMonitorTop([in] long a_lMonID, [out, retval] long *a_plMonitorTop); (It is used to get                               the top co-ordinate of a particular monitor.)
   
           Parameters:
    	     Positive Integer.(Monitor index. It should start from "0")
    
           Returns:
 	     Positive Integer.

5. Method:
    GetMonitorRight([in] long a_lMonID, [out, retval] long *a_plMonitorRight); (It is used to                                get the right co-ordinate of a particular monitor.)
   
           Parameters:
    	     Positive Integer.(Monitor index. It should start from "0")
    
           Returns:
 	     Positive Integer.

6. Method:
    GetMonitorBottom([in] long a_lMonID, [out, retval] long *a_plMonitorBottom); (It is used                                   to get  the bottom co-ordinate of a particular monitor.)
   
           Parameters:
    	     Positive Integer.(Monitor index. It should start from "0")
    
           Returns:
 	     Positive Integer.

Error Handling mechanism:
    It has 2 methods, GetError() and GetErrorMsg() that can return a error 
    code and error message to UI.

   a)GetError([out, retval] long *a_plError); (It is used to get the error code.)
   
           Parameters:
    	     None.
    
           Returns:
 	     Positive Integer.(Error Code).

   b)GetErrorMsg([out, retval] BSTR *a_pbstrErrorMsg); (It is used to get the error                             description.)

          Parameters:
    	     None.
    
           Returns:
 	     String.(Error description in string format.).
